CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 27, 1954, pg. 13 reads: "The Glamorous Cotillion - Scenes from the third annual debutante Cotillion given by Pittsburgh AKAs included...Center right photo: Wilbur H. Sullivan swings his two graceful debutante daughters, Herschelle Sandra nad Paula Kathleen, in the traditional father-daughter waltz..."
TitMainTitle: Wilbur H. Sullivan, dancing waltz with daughters Herschelle Sandra Sullivan and Paula Kathleen Sullivan in Syria Mosque for Alpha Kappa Alpha's 1954 Cotillion
